First step

We’ll use as data the Neo4j Movie Database which contains data about actors/directors and their relationships with movies.

So in Elastic we will create two indexes:

  • movie: which contains the movies
  • person: which contains the people (actors/directors)

In Neo4j we’ll create the following graph structure:

Create the Follwing constraints on Neo4j:

paragraphs.title: Create the Person constraint
paragraphs.text:
%neo4j_polyglot
create constraint on (p:Person) assert p.id is unique;

paragraphs.title: Create the Movie constraint
paragraphs.text:
%neo4j_polyglot
create constraint on (m:Movie) assert m.id is unique;

paragraphs.text:
%neo4j_polyglot
CALL gds.graph.create.cypher(
    'simple-page-rank-catalog',
    'MATCH (p:Person) RETURN id(p) AS id',
    'MATCH (p1:Person)-->()<--(p2:Person) RETURN distinct id(p1) AS source, id(p2) AS target')

paragraphs.title: Execute the Page Rank on Neo4j and stream back the results into Elastic
paragraphs.text:
%neo4j_polyglot
CALL gds.pageRank.stream('simple-page-rank-catalog') YIELD nodeId, score
WITH gds.util.asNode(nodeId) AS p, score
CALL streams.publish('rank', {id: toString(p.id), entity: 'person', properties: {rank: score, name: p.name, born: p.born}})
RETURN p.name, score
ORDER BY score DESC
